# 🎬 IMDb Movie Data Analysis (Python + SQL Approach)

This project performs Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on an IMDb movie dataset using **Python (Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn)** and maps each analysis step to equivalent **SQL queries** used in real-world data analytics.

---

# 📌 1. Dataset Overview

Table Name: `imdb_movies`

Columns:
- imdb_id
- title
- release_date
- genre
- duration
- country
- content_rating
- director
- income
- votes
- score

---

# 🧹 2. Data Cleaning (SQL Equivalent)

## 🗓 Convert release_date to DATE
```sql
ALTER TABLE imdb_movies
ALTER COLUMN release_date DATE;
```

## 📅 Extract Release Year
```sql
SELECT 
    title,
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM release_date) AS release_year
FROM imdb_movies;
```

## 🔢 Convert Numeric Columns
```sql
SELECT 
    CAST(duration AS FLOAT),
    CAST(income AS FLOAT),
    CAST(votes AS INT),
    CAST(score AS FLOAT)
FROM imdb_movies;
```

## ❌ Handle Missing Values
```sql
SELECT *
FROM imdb_movies
WHERE score IS NULL 
   OR duration IS NULL;
```

---

# 📊 3. Basic EDA Queries

## 📦 Dataset Size
```sql
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_movies
FROM imdb_movies;
```

## 📈 Statistical Summary (Example for Score)
```sql
SELECT 
    MIN(score) AS min_score,
    MAX(score) AS max_score,
    AVG(score) AS avg_score,
    COUNT(score) AS total_scores
FROM imdb_movies;
```

---

# 🎬 4. Movies Released Per Year

```sql
SELECT 
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM release_date) AS release_year,
    COUNT(*) AS total_movies
FROM imdb_movies
GROUP BY release_year
ORDER BY release_year;
```

---

# 🎭 5. Top 10 Genres

```sql
SELECT 
    genre,
    COUNT(*) AS total_movies
FROM imdb_movies
GROUP BY genre
ORDER BY total_movies DESC
LIMIT 10;
```

---

# 🌍 6. Top Producing Countries

```sql
SELECT 
    country,
    COUNT(*) AS total_movies
FROM imdb_movies
GROUP BY country
ORDER BY total_movies DESC
LIMIT 10;
```

---

# 💰 7. Income vs Score Analysis

```sql
SELECT 
    title,
    income,
    score
FROM imdb_movies
WHERE income IS NOT NULL 
  AND score IS NOT NULL;
```

To calculate correlation (PostgreSQL example):

```sql
SELECT CORR(income, score) 
FROM imdb_movies;
```

---

# 🏆 8. Top 10 Highest Rated Movies

```sql
SELECT 
    title,
    score
FROM imdb_movies
ORDER BY score DESC
LIMIT 10;
```

---

# 🔥 9. Votes vs Income Relationship

```sql
SELECT 
    votes,
    income
FROM imdb_movies
WHERE votes IS NOT NULL 
  AND income IS NOT NULL;
```

